Villagers facing water scarcity quench thirst from sand trucks trickle             Joseph Muchiri  23rd Sep 2019 00:00:00 GMT +0300 Joseph Muchiri  23rd Sep 2019 00:00:00 GMT +0300 Joseph Muchiri   Residents scoop water from a hole they dug on the bed of River Thuci at Rianjeru area of Mbeere North. The river has dried up after farmers upstream blocked the water flow to collect water for irrigation. [Joseph Muchiri, Standard]   Residents scoop water from a hole they dug on the bed of River Thuci at Rianjeru area of Mbeere North. The river has dried up after farmers upstream blocked the water flow to collect water for irrigation. [Joseph Muchiri, Standard] Residents scoop water from a hole they dug on the bed of River Thuci at Rianjeru area of Mbeere North. The river has dried up after farmers upstream blocked the water flow to collect water for irrigation. [Joseph Muchiri, Standard] Residents scoop water from a hole they dug on the bed of River Thuci at Rianjeru area of Mbeere North. The river has dried up after farmers upstream blocked the water flow to collect water for irrigation.             For More of This and Other Stories, Grab Your Copy of the Standard Newspaper. For More of This and Other Stories, Grab Your Copy of the Standard Newspaper.                        We are undertaking a survey to help us improve our content for you. This will only take 1 minute of your time, please give us your feedback by clicking HERE. All responses will be confidential. We are undertaking a survey to help us improve our content for you. This will only take 1 minute of your time, please give us your feedback by clicking HERE. All responses will be confidential. HERE Related Topics Arid zone Sand trucks Government